Thanks for helping your students experience this opportunity, Canton Preparatory High School, Covenant House Academy - Grand Rapids, Covenant House Academy - Detroit, Michigan Math and Science Academy, Taylor Prep Charter High School, and UPrep Schools.

post_text: The historical Tuskegee Airmen came out Monday to speak to several of our students about their past and what they had to go through during World War 2. This was in recognition of Black History Month, something Covenant House was excited to celebrate. Our eager students even went as far as to raise funds to give back to the Airmen so they can invest more into their museum in Detroit. Check it out!

post_text: The staff at the Central campus began a schoolwide vocabulary program in October that will last until December. Teachers present three new vocabulary words each week by performing a skit which features the words repeatedly, and some teachers even wear signs featuring the words and definitions so students see them repeatedly throughout the day. Research shows that seeing and hearing a word 17 times will cement it into your brain, so the kids are getting repeated exposure in a variety of ways. According to English teacher Mr. Ettlinger, the words -- such as elaborate, interpret,and distinguish -- were carefully chosen because they are cross-curricular, meaning they are used in all classes, and they appear frequently on MME and MEAP tests. The students have been responding to the program with enthusiasm, and are scoring high on informal vocab quizzes on Fridays.
